<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Irene B. Rosenfeld</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Chairman of the Board and</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Chief Executive Officer</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Three Parkway North</P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">March&nbsp;27, 2015 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Dear Fellow Shareholders: </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">I&#146;m pleased to invite you to our 2015 Annual Meeting of Shareholders. We will hold the meeting at 9 a.m. CDT on Wednesday, May&nbsp;20, 2015, at the North Shore
Center for the Performing Arts in Skokie, Ill. The Center will open to shareholders at 8 a.m. If you wish to attend the meeting, we ask that you register in advance by following the instructions included in the Proxy Statement. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">All shareholders of record as of March&nbsp;11, 2015 are entitled to vote. As in the past, we are distributing proxy materials with instructions on how to access these
materials and on how to vote. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Even if you plan to attend the 2015 Annual Meeting of Shareholders in person, we encourage you to vote in advance of the meeting. You
can vote in advance of the meeting in one of three ways: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Visit the website listed on your proxy card/voting instruction form to vote via the Internet; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Call the telephone number on your proxy card/voting instruction form to vote by telephone; or </TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Sign, date and return your proxy card/voting instruction form in the enclosed envelope by mail. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Highlights of Our
2014 Financial and Business Performance: </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Strong Earnings Growth and Margin Expansion </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In 2014, we made good progress on our strategic and financial goals in a very challenging environment. We generated strong earnings growth and margin expansion, while
delivering modest Organic Net Revenue<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP> growth. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Specifically: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="95%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em">


<IMG SRC="g850955g13s86.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">Net revenues were $34.2 billion, down 3.0 percent. Organic Net Revenue<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP> grew 2.4 percent, driven by higher prices in response to higher input costs. Emerging markets<SUP
STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(2)</SUP> continued to grow, with Brazil, Russia and India each up double-digits. Power Brands &#150; our largest, fastest-growing and highest-margin brands that account for over 60 percent of our revenue
&#150; continued to drive our top line and grew at a rate nearly twice as fast as the total company.</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="13"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="13" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em">


<IMG SRC="g850955g13s86.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">Operating income margin declined 170 basis points to 9.5 percent. Adjusted Operating Income<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(3)</SUP> margin increased 80 basis points to 12.9 percent. We accomplished this by pricing
to recover higher input costs, delivering record-high net productivity and aggressively reducing overheads.</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="13"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="13" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em">


<IMG SRC="g850955g13s86.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">On the bottom line, diluted EPS was $1.28, down 41.6 percent, due almost entirely to cycling last year&#146;s arbitration award<SUP
STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(4)</SUP>. Adjusted EPS<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP> increased 23.4 percent on a constant-currency basis, driven mostly by operating gains.</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="13"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="13" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em">


<IMG SRC="g850955g13s86.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">We returned $2.9 billion of cash to our shareholders through share repurchases and dividends.</TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="line-height:6.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #000000;width:31%">&nbsp;</P>

Exhibit A and the section entitled &#147;Non-GAAP Financial Measures&#148; in our Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2014. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

market leader in the &#147;free-from&#148; snacking categories (snacks that are free from the eight most common food allergens). Both acquisitions fit with our strategy to expand our capabilities in key countries or categories.</TD>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Targeting Best-in-Class Cost Management to Expand Margins </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Margin expansion remains a key priority. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We&#146;re advancing our supply chain
reinvention initiative to deliver strong net productivity and move more of the production of our Power Brands to more efficient assets. We&#146;re on track to deliver $3 billion in gross productivity savings, $1.5 billion in net productivity and $1
billion in incremental cash flow from 2014 through 2016. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We&#146;re also driving overheads down by leveraging a zero-based budgeting approach to identify and
capture sustainable cost savings. As part of this, we&#146;re addressing indirect costs as well as headcount costs, and we&#146;re building a global shared services capability, which will allow us to leverage our scale as well as simplify and
standardize our processes globally. As a result of these initiatives, in 2014, we significantly reduced overheads as a percent of revenue. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Generating Strong
Cash Flow and Returning Cash to Shareholders </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Over the past two years, we delivered $4.8 billion of Free Cash Flow excluding items<SUP
STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(6)</SUP>. That&#146;s nearly 30 percent higher than our two-year target of $3.7 billion. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our priorities for use of this
cash continue to be where we believe we can generate attractive financial returns, including: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="97%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:1pt">


<IMG SRC="g850955g89e24.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top">Reinvesting in the business to drive top-tier growth by investing in our Power Brands and routes to market, supporting our supply chain reinvention or investing in shared services</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top">


<IMG SRC="g850955g89e24.jpg" ALT="LOGO">

<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Investing in communities</I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.20em; text-indent:-1.20em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;Investing $50 million in community partnerships to promote healthy lifestyle programs, focused on nutrition education and promoting active lifestyles</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Focus on What We Can Control </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In the current
challenging environment, we&#146;re executing our transformation agenda by controlling what we can control: reducing costs, pricing to protect profitability and driving our Power Brands and innovation platforms in key markets. While we expect the
operating environment to remain difficult in 2015, we&#146;re taking the necessary steps to achieve our near-term financial targets and to promote the long-term health of our business. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">By executing these strategies, we&#146;re well-positioned to deliver strong returns to our shareholders. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">On behalf of all of our Mondel&#275;z International colleagues, I thank you for your continued support of our company. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Best regards, </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">


<IMG SRC="g850955g25u01.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Irene B. Rosenfeld </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Chairman and Chief Executive
Officer </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g850955g88l57.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Forward-Looking Statements </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">This letter
to shareholders contains a number of forward-looking statements. Words, and variations of words, such as &#147;will,&#148; &#147;expect,&#148; &#147;believe,&#148; &#147;positioned,&#148; &#147;target&#148; and similar expressions are intended to
identify our forward-looking statements, including, but not limited to, statements about: our future performance, including our future revenue growth, earnings per share, margins and cash flow; the operating environment; consumer demand;
productivity and productivity savings and improvement; our transformation agenda; our investments and the results of those investments; our operating model; the timeframe for completing the coffee transactions; acquisitions; share repurchases;
dividends; returns to shareholders; and our well-being initiatives. These forward-looking statements are subject to a number of risks and uncertainties, many of which are beyond our control, which could cause our actual results to differ materially
from those indicated in our forward-looking statements. Such factors include, but are not limited to, risks from operating globally and in emerging markets, changes in currency exchange rates, continued volatility of commodity and other input costs,
pricing actions, weakness in economic conditions, weakness in consumer spending, unanticipated disruptions to our business, competition, the restructuring program and our other transformation initiatives not yielding the anticipated benefits,
changes in the assumptions on which the restructuring program is based, failing to successfully complete the coffee transactions on the anticipated time frame and tax law changes. Please also see our risk factors, as they may be amended from time to
time, set forth in our filings with the SEC, including our most recently filed Annual Report on Form 10-K. Mondel&#275;z International disclaims and does not undertake any obligation to update or revise any forward-looking statement in this letter
to shareholders, except as required by applicable law or regulation. </P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:16pt; font-family:ARIAL"><A NAME="toc850955_1"></A>Proxy Statement Summary </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>In this Proxy Statement Summary and throughout the Proxy Statement, &#147;we,&#148; &#147;us,&#148; &#147;our,&#148; &#147;the Company,&#148; and &#147;Mondel&#275;z
International,&#148; refer to Mondel&#275;z International, Inc. </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>This summary highlights select information contained elsewhere in this Proxy Statement. You
should read the entire Proxy Statement carefully before voting and consider all information in the Proxy Statement. For more complete information regarding the Company&#146;s 2014 performance, please see our Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year
ended December&nbsp;31, 2014. </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Annual Meeting of Shareholders </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<B></B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Independent Board.</B> 12 of our 13 current directors are independent. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<IMG SRC="g850955g01r75.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
<B></B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Limitation on Management Directors.</B> Our Chairman and CEO is the only member of management to serve as a director. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<IMG SRC="g850955g01r75.jpg" ALT="LOGO">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Independent Lead Director Provides Independent Leadership of the Board&#146;s Work.</B> Annually, our independent directors select our Lead Director, who has broad substantive responsibilities and powers. Those
include presiding at executive sessions of independent directors and approving board schedules, meeting agendas and materials. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:right; width:48%;padding-right:9pt;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>ITEM&nbsp;2. Advisory Vote to Approve Executive Compensation (Page 78 of this Proxy Statement)
</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Compensation Goals </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our Human Resources and Compensation Committee
has four primary goals for our executive compensation program: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">1.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Attract, retain and motivate talented executive officers and develop world-class business leaders; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">2.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Support business strategies that promote superior long-term shareholder returns; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">3.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Align pay and performance by making a significant portion of our Named Executive Officers&#146; compensation dependent on achieving financial and other critical strategic and individual goals; and </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">4.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Align our Named Executive Officers&#146; and shareholders&#146; interests through stock ownership guidelines and equity-based incentive grants that link executive compensation to sustained and superior Total Shareholder
Return<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1).</SUP> </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Compensation Design </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We design our executive compensation program to achieve these goals by: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Linking pay to performance; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

independent registered public accountants for the year ending December&nbsp;31, 2015. We provide information on fees billed by PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP in 2014 and 2013 on page&nbsp;28 of this Proxy Statement. </P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Other Matters </B></P>

Annual Meeting may refuse to allow presentation of an improperly submitted proposal or a nomination for the Board at the Annual Meeting. We described the requirements for shareholders to properly submit proposals and nominations at the Annual
Meeting in our 2014 Proxy Statement. Those requirements are similar to those described under &#147;2016 Annual Meeting of Shareholders&#148; in this Proxy Statement. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">If any other matters properly come before the Annual Meeting, your proxy authorizes the designated proxies to vote on such matters in accordance with their best
judgment. </P>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:16pt; font-family:ARIAL"><A NAME="toc850955_2"></A>ITEM&nbsp;1. Election of Directors </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc850955_3"></A>Process for Nominating Directors </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Governance, Membership and Public Affairs Committee of our Board of Directors (the &#147;Governance Committee&#148;) is responsible for identifying, evaluating and
recommending to the Board director nominees for election at the 2015 Annual Meeting of Shareholders (and any adjournments or postponements of the meeting) (the &#147;Annual Meeting&#148;). The Governance Committee invites director nominee
suggestions from the directors, shareholders, management and others. From time to time, the Governance Committee retains third-party executive search firms to assist in identifying and evaluating potential director nominees based on the Board&#146;s
recruitment objectives. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>General Qualifications </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board believes all
directors should possess certain personal characteristics, including integrity, sound business judgment and vision. The Board believes these characteristics are necessary to establish a competent, ethical and well-functioning Board that best
represents the interests of our shareholders. Under our Corporate Governance Guidelines (the &#147;Guidelines&#148;), when evaluating the suitability of individuals for nomination, the Governance Committee takes into account many factors. These
include the individual&#146;s general understanding of the varied disciplines relevant to the success of a large, publicly traded company in today&#146;s global business environment, understanding of our global businesses and markets, professional
expertise and educational background and other factors that promote diversity of views, knowledge and experience. The Governance Committee also considers an individual&#146;s ability to devote sufficient time and effort to fulfill his or her
responsibilities to the Company, taking into account the individual&#146;s other commitments. In addition, the Governance Committee considers whether an individual meets various independence requirements, including whether his or her service on
boards and committees of other organizations is consistent with our conflicts of interest policy. The Governance Committee also evaluates each individual in the context of the Board as a whole, with the objective of recruiting and recommending a
slate of director nominees who can best perpetuate the Company&#146;s success and represent our shareholder&#146;s interests through the exercise of sound judgment and informed decision-making. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In addition, under our Guidelines, the Governance Committee generally will not recommend, and the Board will not nominate an individual or re-nominate for election an
independent director after he or she reaches age 75. However, the Governance Committee and Board may do so in extraordinary circumstances if nomination or re-nomination is in&nbsp;the shareholders&#146; best interests because the candidate is
uniquely qualified to contribute to a specific dimension of the Board&#146;s work and the Company&#146;s growth in the subsequent year. If the Governance Committee determines that the individual&#146;s nomination or re-nomination for election is in
the shareholders&#146; best interests, the Governance Committee may recommend, and the Board may approve, that director&#146;s nomination or re-nomination for up to three annual terms following the director&#146;s 75th birthday. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Further, a management director must resign from the Board upon ceasing to be a Company officer. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Individual Experience, Qualifications, Attributes and Skills </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Governance
Committee works with the Board to determine the appropriate mix of characteristics, professional experience and areas of expertise that will result in a Board that is strong in its collective knowledge, allowing the Board to fulfill its
responsibilities and best perpetuate our long-term success and represent all shareholders&#146; interests. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Under the leadership of the Lead Director and Chairman
of the Governance Committee, the Governance Committee annually conducts evaluations of the Board and the Board&#146;s committees and coordinates the directors&#146; self-assessments that assess the experience, qualifications, attributes, skills,
diversity and contributions of each individual and of the Board as a whole. Every year, the director nominees complete questionnaires to update and confirm their background, qualifications, skills and potential conflicts of interest. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">As noted above, the Guidelines provide that the Governance Committee will consider factors that promote diversity of views, knowledge and experience when evaluating the
suitability of individuals for nomination. While the Board has no formal written policy regarding what specific factors would create such diversity, the Governance Committee </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;7 </FONT></P>

recognizes the significant benefit diversity provides to the Board and Mondel&#275;z International, as varying viewpoints contribute to a more informed and effective decision-making process. The
Governance Committee seeks broad experience in relevant industries, professions and areas of expertise important to our operations. Among them are: industry knowledge; substantial global business and other international experience and backgrounds
given our global, multicultural business; significant operating experience; leadership and people development experience; accounting and financial expertise; product development and marketing experience; and public company board and corporate
governance experience. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our director nominees&#146; varied and relevant experiences, global and diverse perspectives, backgrounds, and personal characteristics
provide the Board with a diversity of viewpoints and enable it to represent effectively our shareholders: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

diversity efforts as part of its periodic assessment of the composition of the Board. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Size of Board </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our Board currently has 13 directors. Ratan N. Tata is not standing for re-election. Accordingly, the Board reduced the size of the Board from 13 and fixed it at 12
effective concurrent with the election of directors at the 2015 Annual Meeting. The Governance Committee recommended and the Board nominated each of the 12 incumbent directors listed below under &#147;Director Nominees for Election at the 2015
Annual Meeting&#148; for election at the 2015 Annual Meeting. Each director nominee consented to his or her nomination for election to the Board. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Annual
Elections </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Shareholders elect all directors annually. Of the 12 directors standing for election, shareholders elected 11 to one-year terms at the 2014 Annual
Meeting of Shareholders. Joseph Neubauer was recommended to the Board as a director nominee by the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer. The Board appointed Mr.&nbsp;Neubauer, effective November&nbsp;21, 2014. The terms of all directors elected at
the 2015 Annual Meeting will end at the 2016 Annual Meeting of Shareholders or when a director&#146;s successor has been duly elected and qualified. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Shareholder
Nominee Recommendations </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Governance Committee welcomes shareholder recommendations of candidates for election to the Board. To recommend a particular
candidate for consideration, the shareholder should submit the required information to our Corporate Secretary, which information includes the name of the recommended candidate along with the same information required for a shareholder to nominate a
candidate for election to the Board at an Annual Meeting and in the same manner as set forth in the Company&#146;s By-Laws. When evaluating a candidate recommended by shareholders, the Governance Committee uses the same criteria set forth in the
Guidelines, as described above under &#147;Item 1. Election of Directors &#150; Process for Nominating Directors,&#148; as it uses to evaluate a candidate the Governance Committee identifies. It then makes a recommendation to the Board regarding the
candidate&#146;s appointment or nomination for election to the Board at an upcoming annual meeting. After the Board&#146;s consideration of the Committee&#146;s recommendation, our Corporate Secretary notifies that shareholder of the Board&#146;s
decision whether to appoint or nominate the candidate. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;8 </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc850955_4"></A>Director Nominees for Election at the 2015 Annual Meeting </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board believes that each director nominee for election at the Annual Meeting is highly qualified. The director nominees&#146; biographies (below) describe the
specific experience, qualifications, attributes and skills that the Governance Committee relied upon when determining to nominate the individual director nominees for election. A particular director nominee may possess other skills, knowledge or
experience in addition to those described below. As their biographies indicate, all the director nominees possess significant leadership and professional experience, knowledge, including industry knowledge, and skills that qualify them for service
on our Board. Each director nominee, other than Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld, satisfies independence requirements under the NASDAQ listing standards and the Board&#146;s categorical standards of director independence. All director nominees satisfy the
criteria stated in our Guidelines and possess the personal characteristics essential for the proper and effective functioning of the Board. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Individual
Nominees&#146; Experience, Qualifications, Attributes and Skills </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The following information regarding each director nominee is as of March&nbsp;11, 2015. It
includes information about each director nominee&#146;s professional experience, educational background, attributes and qualifications that led the Board to nominate him or her for election. It also includes information about U.S. publicly listed
company directorships held currently and during the past five years. The director nominees may also serve on the boards of various private and non-U.S. companies and charitable, educational and cultural institutions, not all of which are included in
their biographies. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The persons named as proxies on each shareholder&#146;s proxy card will vote the shares represented by the proxy card FOR or AGAINST the
director nominees or ABSTAIN from voting, as indicated in the shareholder&#146;s voting instructions. If a director nominee should become unavailable to serve as a director, the persons named as proxies intend to vote the shares for a replacement
director nominee designated by the Board. In lieu of naming a substitute, the Board may reduce the number of directors on our Board. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>THE BOARD RECOMMENDS
SHAREHOLDERS VOTE FOR THE ELECTION OF EACH OF THESE TWELVE DIRECTOR NOMINEES. </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Director since April 2007</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Current Committee:</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.00em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Chair, Governance, Membership and Public Affairs</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.00em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;As Lead Director, an <I>ex-officio</I> member of all committees of which he is not a member</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Age: 65</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. Ketchum served as President and Chief Executive Officer of Newell Rubbermaid Inc., a global marketer of
consumer and commercial products, from October 2005 until his retirement in June 2011 and was a member of its board of directors from November 2004 to May 2012. From 1971 to 2004, Mr. Ketchum served in a variety of roles of increasing responsibility
at The Procter &amp; Gamble Company, a global marketer of consumer products, including President, Global Baby and Family Care, from 1999 to 2004, President &#150; North American Paper Sector from 1996 to 1999, and Vice President and General Manager
&#150; Tissue/Towel from 1990 to 1996.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Education:</I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. Ketchum received a Bachelor of Science in Industrial Engineering and Operations Research from Cornell University.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Public Company Board:</I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. Ketchum was formerly a director of Newell Rubbermaid Inc.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. Reynolds served as Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of CBS Corporation, a mass media
company, from January 2006 until his retirement in August 2009. From September 2001 until December 2005, Mr.&nbsp;Reynolds served as President and Chief Executive Officer of Viacom Television Stations Group and as Executive Vice President and Chief
Financial Officer of Viacom Inc., a mass media company, from May 2000 to September 2001. He also served as Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of CBS Corporation and its predecessor, Westinghouse Electric Corporation, from 1994 to
2000. Prior to that, Mr.&nbsp;Reynolds served in various capacities at PepsiCo, Inc., a food and beverage company, for twelve years, including Chief Financial Officer or Financial Officer at Pizza Hut, Pepsi Cola International, Kentucky Fried
Chicken Worldwide and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Frito-Lay.</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. Reynolds is a
Certified Public Accountant.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Education:</I></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Ratan Tata to Become Special Advisor to the Chairman and CEO </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In February 2015, the Board named Ratan N. Tata as Special Advisor to the Chairman and CEO for one year effective upon his retirement from the Board at the
Company&#146;s 2015 Annual Meeting. The Board did so because of Mr.&nbsp;Tata&#146;s unique experience and expertise in leading a successful global enterprise; knowledge of Indian, Asian and emerging markets and cultural affairs; support for the
development and promotion of innovative business practices; and insights into the continuing evolution of consumer products. The role is unpaid. The Company will reimburse reasonable expenses related to the role. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:16pt; font-family:ARIAL"><A NAME="toc850955_5"></A>Corporate Governance </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We believe that a strong corporate
governance framework is essential to our long-term success. This section describes our governance policies, key governance practices and Board leadership structure and oversight functions. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc850955_6"></A>Governance Guidelines </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board
adopted Guidelines articulating our governance philosophy, practices and policies in a range of areas, including: the Board&#146;s role and responsibilities; Board composition and structure; responsibilities of the committees of the Board; CEO and
Board performance evaluations; and succession planning. At least annually, the Governance Committee reviews the Guidelines and recommends any changes to the Board. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc850955_7"></A>Key Corporate Governance Practices </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">At least annually, we review our corporate governance practices to support the Board&#146;s independent leadership, accountability and oversight: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Annual Election of Directors</I>. Our By-Laws provide that our shareholders elect all directors annually. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Majority Voting in Uncontested Director Elections</I>. Our By-Laws provide that, in uncontested elections, director nominees must be elected by a majority of the votes cast. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Special Meetings of Shareholders</I>. Our By-Laws allow shareholders of record of at least twenty percent (20%)&nbsp;of the voting power of the outstanding stock to call a special meeting of shareholders.
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Limitation on Management Directors</I>. Our Guidelines provide that the Board believes the Chairman and CEO generally should be the only member of management to serve as a director. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Independent Committees</I>. The Board has determined that all Board committees should consist entirely of, and be chaired by, independent directors. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Executive Sessions</I>. At each in-person Board meeting, our independent directors meet without the CEO or any other members of management present to discuss substantive issues important to Mondel&#275;z
International, including matters concerning management. The Lead Director chairs these sessions. In some instances, a committee chair leads Board discussion of a topic relevant to that committee&#146;s remit. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Board, Committee and Director Self-Assessments.</I> The Governance Committee establishes processes for annual Board, committee and individual director self-assessments. The Board, committees and management use the
results of these self-assessments in planning their work and subsequent governance decisions. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Shareholder Engagement</I>. We promote ongoing dialogue with shareholders throughout the year. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Annual Chairman and CEO Evaluation</I>. The Human Resources and Compensation Committee (the &#147;Compensation Committee&#148;) annually evaluates the Chairman and CEO&#146;s performance. The Compensation Committee
seeks input from the other directors regarding her performance before deciding her performance rating. The Governance Committee annually considers the CEO&#146;s performance and suitability as Chairman when determining whether to nominate her for
re-election. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt"><I>Stock Holding Requirements</I>. To promote alignment of directors&#146; and shareholders&#146; interests, our Guidelines provide that we expect directors to
hold Mondel&#275;z International common stock in an amount equal to five times the annual Board retainer within five years of&nbsp;joining the Board. As of March&nbsp;11, 2015, </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;19 </FONT></P>

deferred stock units. Distribution of actual shares occurs six months after the director ends his or her service as a director. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Leadership Structure. </I>Our Guidelines currently provide for an independent Lead Director and that the CEO also serves as Chairman of the Board. See additional discussion below under &#147;&#150;&nbsp;Board
Leadership Structure.&#148; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Special Meetings of the Board</I>. Our By-Laws empower both the Lead Director and the Chairman to call special meetings of the Board. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc850955_8"></A>Board Leadership Structure </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our
By-Laws provide the Board flexibility in determining its leadership structure. The Board may appoint and designate the duties of a&nbsp;Lead Director and permit one person to hold both the offices of CEO and Chairman. Within that framework, the
Board annually re-evaluates its leadership structure to determine the most appropriate leadership structure at that time. In considering which leadership structure will allow it to most effectively carry out its responsibilities and best represent
shareholders&#146; interests, the Board takes into account various factors. Among them are our specific business needs, our operating and financial performance, industry conditions, economic and regulatory environments, results of Board and
committee annual self-assessments, advantages and disadvantages of alternative leadership structures based on circumstances at that time and our corporate governance practices. In keeping with this principle, the Board may determine that the CEO
also serve as Chairman, but if it does so, it also appoints an independent lead director with robust responsibilities. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Current Leadership Structure </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Currently, our Guidelines provide that: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">an independent director serves as Lead Director; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">independent directors chair the Board&#146;s four standing committees; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">the CEO serves as Chairman of the Board. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board believes that this leadership structure provided an effective
balance of strong leadership and independent oversight and best meets our current circumstances and anticipated needs. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Independent Director Leadership and
Oversight </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board believes that robust independent Board leadership and oversight are very important. Therefore, it established the substantive position of
independent Lead Director for times when one individual serves as both Chairman and CEO. Our independent directors annually select our Lead Director for a one-year term. The Board created the Lead Director position to provide independent leadership
of the Board&#146;s affairs on behalf of our shareholders, increase the Board&#146;s effectiveness, promote open communication amongst the independent directors and serve as the principal liaison between the Chairman and the other independent
directors. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Lead Director Role and Responsibilities </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Under our
Guidelines, the Lead Director, in consultation with the other independent directors, has the following duties and responsibilities: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Serve as liaison between the independent directors and the Chairman and CEO; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">With respect to long-term meeting planning, seek input from the independent directors and advise the Chairman and CEO as to an appropriate annual schedule of and major agenda topics for regular Board meetings prior to
Board review and approval; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">With respect to specific Board meetings, seek input from the independent directors regarding agenda items and the content of briefing materials. Add agenda items in his or her discretion. Review and approve meeting
agenda as well as the content of Board briefing materials; </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Facilitate effective communication and interaction between the Board and management. To assist the Lead Director in fulfilling this responsibility, the Board may adopt more specific procedures designed to promote
effective communication and interaction while minimizing disruption of the Company&#146;s day-to-day activities; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Be available for consultation and direct communication with the Company&#146;s major shareholders; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Perform such other duties as the Board may from time to time delegate to the Lead Director. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Having established a
substantive Lead Director position, the Board selects a highly capable individual from amongst our skilled and experienced independent directors to provide robust independent leadership. Mark D. Ketchum is our current Lead Director. The independent
directors first appointed him to that role in 2009 and have re-appointed him annually. The independent directors believe that he is an effective Lead Director due to his independence, leadership, global operating experience as former President and
Chief Executive Officer of Newell Rubbermaid Inc. and a variety of roles during his 33 year career at The Procter&nbsp;&amp; Gamble Company, and corporate governance experience, including his prior service as director of Newell Rubbermaid Inc. and
Hillenbrand Industries. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Chairman and CEO Role and Responsibilities </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld has served as our CEO and as a director since June 2006. In conjunction with our 2007 spin-off from Altria Group, Inc., the Board concluded that
Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld should also serve as Chairman because of her extensive knowledge of the Company, the food industry and the competitive environment in which we operate, her leadership experience and her ability and dedication to working closely
with the Lead Director and our other independent directors. Based on our current circumstances and anticipated needs, the Board continues to believe that having Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld serve as both CEO and Chairman serves our shareholders&#146;
interests and contributes to the Board&#146;s efficiency and effectiveness. The Board believes that she is generally in the best position to inform our independent directors about our global operations and critical business matters and ensure
alignment of our business and strategic plans. Further, the Board believes that combining these roles also fosters expedient communication between Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld and the Board. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc850955_9"></A>Director Independence </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our
Guidelines require that at least 80% of our directors meet the NASDAQ listing standards&#146; independence requirements and provide that the Chairman and CEO generally should be the only&nbsp;member of management to serve as a director. In order to
determine that a director is independent, the Board must&nbsp;affirmatively determine, after reviewing all relevant information, that a director has no relationship with Mondel&#275;z International or any of its subsidiaries that would interfere
with the exercise of independent judgment in carrying out&nbsp;the responsibilities of a director. To assist in this determination, the Board adopted categorical standards of director&nbsp;independence, including whether a director or a member of
the director&#146;s immediate family has&nbsp;any current&nbsp;or past employment or affiliation with Mondel&#275;z International or our independent registered public accountants. Annex A to the Guidelines lists these categorical standards. It is
available on our website at <I><U><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">www.mondelezinternational.com/investors/corporate-governance</FONT></U></I>. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;21 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board determined that, under our categorical standards and NASDAQ&#146;s listing standards, the following
directors&nbsp;are independent: Stephen F. Bollenbach, Lewis W.K. Booth, Lois D. Juliber, Mark D. Ketchum, Jorge S. Mesquita, Joseph Neubauer, Nelson Peltz, Fredric G. Reynolds, Patrick T. Siewert, Ruth J. Simmons, Ratan N. Tata and
Jean-Fran&ccedil;ois&nbsp;
M. L. van Boxmeer. Irene B. Rosenfeld is not independent because she is a Mondel&#275;z International employee. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc850955_10"></A>Oversight
 of Risk Management </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our business faces various risks, including strategic, financial, operational and compliance risks. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Management is responsible for the day-to-day assessment, management and mitigation of risk. Identifying, managing and mitigating our exposure to these risks and effectively overseeing this process are critical to our
operational decision-making and annual planning processes. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Our Board has ultimate responsibility for risk oversight, but it has delegated primary responsibility for overseeing risk assessment and management to the Audit Committee. Pursuant to its charter, the Audit Committee
reviews and discusses risk assessment and risk management guidelines, policies and processes utilized in our Enterprise Risk Management (&#147;ERM&#148;) process. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our ERM process is ongoing and implemented at all levels of our operations and across business units to identify, assess, monitor, manage and mitigate risk. Our ERM
process facilitates open communication between management and the Board so that the Board and committees understand key risks to our business and performance, our risk management process and how it is functioning, the participants in the process and
the information gathered through the process. The Audit Committee annually reviews the functioning of our ERM process as well as the results of our annual ERM risk assessment. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Annually, the Audit Committee reviews and approves management&#146;s recommendation for allocating to the full Board or retaining for itself responsibility for
reviewing and assessing key risk exposures and management&#146;s response to those exposures. Management provides reports to the Board and Audit Committee in advance of meetings regarding key risks and the actions management has taken to monitor,
control and mitigate these risks. Management also attends Board and Audit Committee meetings to discuss these reports and provide any updates. The Audit Committee reports key risk discussions to the Board following its meetings. Board members may
also further discuss the risk management process directly with members of management. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;22 </FONT></P>

practices for all employees (including executives)</P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Succession planning</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Human resources policies and practices</P></TD></TR>
