<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(1)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">For a discussion about risk oversight relating to our compensation programs, see &#147;Board Committees and Membership &#150; Human Resources and Compensation Committee &#150; How the Compensation Committee Manages
Compensation-Related Risk.&#148; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board frequently discusses our strategic plans, issues and opportunities in light of circumstances in the food
and beverage industry and the economic environment. Additionally, the Board devotes several days each year to a highly-focused review of our strategic plans, including strategic and operational risks. More generally, the Board is responsible for
oversight of strategy, broad corporate policy and overall performance of the Company through engaged oversight of management. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board believes our current
leadership structure enhances its oversight of risk management because our CEO, who is ultimately responsible for our risk management process, is in the best position as Chairman to discuss with the Board these key risks and management&#146;s
responses to them. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc850955_11"></A>Codes of Conduct </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Code of Business Conduct and Ethics for Non-Employee Directors </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We have
adopted a Code of Business Conduct and Ethics for Non-Employee Directors (the &#147;Directors Ethics Code&#148;). It fosters a culture of honesty and integrity, focuses on areas of ethical risk, guides non-employee directors in recognizing and
handling ethical issues and provides mechanisms to report unethical conduct. Annually, each non-employee director must acknowledge in writing that he or she has received, reviewed and understands the Directors Ethics Code. Shareholders and others
can access our Director Ethics Code on our website at <I><U>www.mondelezinternational.com/investors/corporate-governance</U>.</I> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Code of Conduct for Employees
</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We have adopted a Code of Conduct that applies to all of our employees. It includes policies that cover ethical and legal practices for nearly every aspect of
our business. The Code of Conduct reflects our values and contains important rules our employees must follow when conducting business. The Code of Conduct is part of our global compliance and integrity program. The program provides training
throughout our Company and encourages reporting of wrongdoing by offering anonymous reporting options and a non-retaliation policy. Shareholders and others can access our Code of Conduct on our website at
<I><U>www.mondelezinternational.com/about-us/compliance-and-integrity</U></I>. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;23 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We will disclose in the Corporate Governance section of our website any amendments to our Directors Ethics Code or Code of
Conduct and any waiver granted to an executive officer or director under these codes. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc850955_12"></A>Review of Transactions with
Related Persons </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Related Persons Policy and Procedures </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board has
adopted a written policy regarding the review, approval or ratification of &#147;related person transactions.&#148; A related person transaction is one in which Mondel&#275;z International is a participant, the amount&nbsp;involved exceeds $120,000
and any &#147;related person&#148; had, has or will have a direct or indirect material&nbsp;interest. In general, &#147;related persons&#148; are the following persons and their immediate family members: our directors, executive officers and
shareholders beneficially owning more than 5% of our outstanding common stock. In accordance with this policy, the Governance Committee reviews transactions that might qualify as related person transactions. If the Governance Committee determines
that a transaction qualifies as a related person transaction, then the Governance Committee reviews, and approves, disapproves or ratifies the related person transaction. The Governance Committee approves or ratifies only those related person
transactions that are fair and reasonable to Mondel&#275;z International and in our and our&nbsp;shareholders&#146; best interests. The chair of the Governance Committee reviews and approves or ratifies potential related person&nbsp;transactions
when it is not practicable or desirable to delay review of a transaction until a committee meeting.&nbsp;The chair reports to the Governance Committee any transaction so approved or ratified. The Governance Committee, in the course of its
review&nbsp;and approval or ratification of a related person transaction under this policy, considers, among other things: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">its commercial reasonableness; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">the materiality of the related person&#146;s direct or indirect interest in it; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">whether it may involve an actual, or create the appearance of a, conflict of interest; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">its impact on the related person&#146;s independence (as defined in our Guidelines and the NASDAQ listing standards); and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">whether it would violate any provision of our Directors Ethics Code or Code of Conduct. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Any member of the Governance
Committee who is a related person with respect to a transaction under review may not participate in the deliberations or decisions regarding the transaction. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Review of Transactions </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">On February&nbsp;9, 2015, BlackRock, Inc.
(&#147;BlackRock&#148;), an investment management corporation, filed a Schedule 13G/A with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (&#147;SEC&#148;) reporting that it was a greater than 5% shareholder as of December&nbsp;31, 2014.&nbsp;During
2014, BlackRock acted as an investment manager with respect to certain investment options under our 401(k) plans for U.S. employees and pension plans for employees in Canada, Ireland and the United Kingdom. BlackRock was selected as an investment
manager for the 401(k) and pension plans by each plan&#146;s designated authority for plan investments. BlackRock&#146;s selection was based on the determination of each plan&#146;s designated authority that the selection met applicable standards
and that the fees were reasonable and appropriate. BlackRock was paid fees, approximately $2.28 million during 2014, from the assets of the specific plans for which it performed services. The Governance Committee reviewed these relationships with
BlackRock and ratified these transactions. The 401(k) and pension plans expect to pay similar fees to BlackRock during 2015 for similar services. (Fees, based on plan asset value, are paid quarterly on a lagging basis.) </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc850955_13"></A>Shareholder Engagement </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We
regularly meet with and seek feedback from our shareholders on a wide range of matters. During 2014, senior management, Investor Relations and the Corporate Secretary engaged with many of our largest shareholders. These meetings were candid and
constructive. We will continue to solicit and consider our shareholders&#146; perspectives. Our Lead Director is available for consultation and direct communication with major shareholders. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;24 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc850955_14"></A>Communications with the Board </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Information for shareholders and other parties interested in communicating with the Lead Director, the Board or our independent directors, individually or as a group,
is available on our website at <I><U>www.mondelezinternational.com/Investors/corporate-governance#contacts</U>.</I> Our Corporate Secretary: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Forwards communications relating to matters within the Board&#146;s purview to the Lead Director or appropriate independent director(s) and communications relating to matters within a Board committee&#146;s area of
responsibility to the chair of the appropriate committee. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Forwards communications relating to ordinary business matters, such as suggestions, inquiries and consumer complaints, to the appropriate Mondel&#275;z International executive or employee, but makes them available to
any independent director who requests them. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Does not forward or retain solicitations, junk mail and obviously frivolous or inappropriate communications. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:16pt; font-family:ARIAL"><A NAME="toc850955_15">
</A>Board Committees and Membership </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Governance Committee considers and makes recommendations to the Board regarding the Board&#146;s committee&nbsp;structure
and membership. Our Board designates the committee members and chairs following consideration of the&nbsp;Governance Committee&#146;s recommendations. The Board has adopted a written charter for each standing committee. The charters define each
committee&#146;s roles and&nbsp;responsibilities. Charters for each committee are available on our website at <U>www.mondelezinternational.com/investors/corporate-governance</U>. Independent directors comprise 100% of the Audit, Compensation,
Finance and Governance Committees. All committee chairs are independent. Each committee meets regularly in executive session without management. Committee Chairs approve agendas and materials for their committee meetings. In addition, committees may
retain outside legal, financial and other advisors, at the Company&#146;s expense. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Based on the results of the annual Board self-assessment process and at the
Governance Committee&#146;s recommendation, the Board established a Finance Committee and appointed its members and chair effective January&nbsp;26, 2015. The Board now has four standing committees: Audit, Finance, Governance, Membership and Public
Affairs and Human Resources and Compensation. The committee structure and membership is as follows: </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc850955_16"></A>Committee
Membership<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP> Effective January&nbsp;26, 2015 </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(6)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Compensation Committee acted once by unanimous written consent during 2014. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc850955_17">
</A>Meeting Attendance </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We expect directors to attend all Board meetings, the Annual Meeting and all meetings of the committees on which they serve. We
understand, however, that occasionally a director may be unable to attend a meeting. The Board held twelve meetings during 2014 and acted three times by unanimous written consent. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">All incumbent directors who served for some or all of 2014 attended at least 75% of the aggregate number of meetings of the Board and all committees on which they served (held during the period that they served), except
Mr.&nbsp;Tata. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">During 2014, Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld and Messrs. Ketchum, Neubauer, Peltz and Reynolds attended 100% and Mmes. Juliber and Simmons and Messrs. Bollenbach, Booth, Mesquita, Siewert and van Boxmeer attended at least 93% of
meetings of the Board and all committees on which they served. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">All of the then-incumbent directors attended the 2014 Annual Meeting of Shareholders. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc850955_18">
</A>Audit Committee </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board established the Audit Committee in accordance with Section&nbsp;3(a)(58)(A) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 (the
&#147;Exchange Act&#148;). The Board has determined that all of the Audit Committee members are independent within the meaning of the NASDAQ listing standards, the New York Stock Exchange listing standards and Rule
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10A-3</FONT> of the Exchange Act. The Board also determined that all Audit Committee members are able to read and understand financial statements in accordance with NASDAQ listing standards and are financially
literate in accordance with the New York Stock Exchange listing standards. Stephen F. Bollenbach and Fredric G. Reynolds are <I>&#147;</I>audit committee financial experts&#148; within the meaning of SEC regulations and have financial sophistication
in accordance with NASDAQ listing standards. No Audit Committee member received any payments in 2014 from us other than compensation for service as a director. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Under its charter, the Audit Committee is responsible for overseeing our accounting and financial reporting processes and audits of our financial statements. The Audit
Committee is directly responsible for the appointment, compensation, retention and oversight of our independent registered public accountants, including review of their qualifications, independence and performance. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Among other duties, the Audit Committee also oversees: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">the integrity of our financial statements, our accounting and financial reporting processes, and our systems of internal control over financial reporting and safeguarding our assets; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">our compliance with legal and regulatory requirements; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">the performance of our internal auditors and internal audit functions; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">our guidelines and policies with respect to risk assessment and risk management. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Audit Committee has established
procedures for the receipt, retention and treatment, on a confidential basis, of any complaints we receive. We encourage employees and third-party individuals and organizations to report concerns about our accounting controls, auditing matters or
anything else that appears to involve financial or other wrongdoing. To report such matters, please e-mail us at: <I><U>mdlz-financialintegrity@mdlz.com</U></I>. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><div style="width:100%;margin-left:0%; margin-right:0%;background-color:#eaeaea;padding-top:2pt;padding-bottom:3pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-top:6pt; margin-left:2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc850955_19"></A>Audit Committee Report for the Year Ended December&nbsp;31, 2014 </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-bottom:6pt; margin-left:2%; margin-right:2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Management has primary responsibility for Mondel&#275;z International&#146;s financial statements and the reporting
process, including the systems of internal control over financial reporting. Our role as the Audit Committee of the Mondel&#275;z International Board of Directors is to oversee Mondel&#275;z International&#146;s accounting and financial </P></div>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

accountants to, among other things: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Discussed with the independent registered public accountants their independence from Mondel&#275;z International, including reviewing non-audit services and fees to assure compliance with (i)&nbsp;regulations
prohibiting the independent registered public accountants from performing specified services that could impair their independence, and (ii)&nbsp;Mondel&#275;z International&#146;s and the Audit Committee&#146;s policies. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2%; margin-right:2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Based upon the reports and discussions described in this report and without other independent verification, and subject to the
limitations of our role and responsibilities outlined in this report and in our written charter, we recommended to the Board, and the Board approved, that the audited consolidated financial statements be included in Mondel&#275;z
International&#146;s Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2014, which was filed with the U. S. Securities and Exchange Commission on February&nbsp;20, 2015. </P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc850955_20"></A>Pre-Approval Policies </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our Audit Committee&#146;s
policy is to pre-approve all audit and non-audit services provided by the independent registered public accountants. These services may include audit services, audit-related services, tax services and other permissible non-audit services. The
pre-approval authority details the particular service or category of service that the independent registered public accountants will perform. Management reports at committee meetings throughout the year on the actual fees charged by the independent
registered public accountants for each category of service. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">During the year, circumstances may arise when it becomes necessary to engage the independent registered
public accountants for additional services not contemplated in the original pre-approval authority. In those instances, the committee approves the services before we engage the independent registered public accountants. In case approval is needed
before a scheduled committee meeting, the committee has delegated pre-approval authority to its chair. The chair must report on such pre-approval decisions at the committee&#146;s next regular meeting. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Audit Committee pre-approved all 2014 audit and non-audit services provided by the independent registered public accountants. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc850955_21"></A>Independent Registered Public Accountants&#146; Fees </B></P>

<TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Audit Fees include (a)&nbsp;the integrated audit of our consolidated financial statements, including statutory audits of the financial
statements of our affiliates, and our internal control over financial reporting and (b)&nbsp;the reviews of our unaudited condensed consolidated interim financial statements (quarterly financial statements). </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Audit-Related Fees include professional services in connection with employee benefit plan audits, due diligence related to acquisitions and divestitures and procedures
related to various other audit and special reports. In 2014, audit-related fees include due diligence and other work related to the planned coffee business divestiture. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Tax Fees include professional services in connection with tax compliance and advice. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">All Other Fees include professional services in connection with seminars, compliance reviews and data protection compliance reviews. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">All fees above include out-of-pocket expenses. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc850955_22">
</A>Finance Committee </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Finance Committee was established effective January&nbsp;26, 2015. The Board has determined that all of the Finance Committee members
are independent within the meaning of the NASDAQ listing standards. The Finance Committee&#146;s charter sets out its responsibilities, which include reviewing and making recommendations to the Board on significant financial matters, including: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">our long-term capital structure including financing plans, projected financial structure, funding requirements, target credit ratings and return on invested capital; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>

<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">authorization of issuances, sales or repurchases of equity and debt securities; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">our external dividend policy and dividend recommendations; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">proposed acquisitions, divestitures, joint ventures, investments, asset sales and purchase commitments in excess of $100 million; and </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Board authorization and delegation levels with respect to financing matters. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Finance Committee also reviews and
discusses with management: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc850955_23"></A>Governance, Membership and Public Affairs Committee </B></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc850955_24"></A>Human Resources and Compensation Committee </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc850955_25"></A>Human Resources and Compensation Committee Independence, Interlocks and Insider Participation </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board has determined that all of the Compensation Committee members are independent within the meaning of the NASDAQ listing standards, including the heightened
independence criteria for compensation committee members. None of the Compensation Committee&#146;s members is or was: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">an officer or employee of Mondel&#275;z International; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>

Persons&#148; above); or </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">an executive officer of another entity at which one of our executive officers serves on the board of directors or the Compensation Committee. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc850955_26"></A>Responsibilities </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation

compensation; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">review and discuss with management the Compensation Discussion and Analysis, and prepare and approve the Compensation Committee&#146;s report to shareholders included in our Proxy Statement; and </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">assess the independence of the Compensation Committee&#146;s outside advisors and at least annually assess whether the work of its compensation consultants has raised any conflict of interest that must be disclosed in
our annual report and Proxy Statement. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation Committee has the authority to delegate any of its responsibilities to the committee&#146;s
Chair, another Compensation Committee member or a subcommittee of Compensation Committee members, unless prohibited by law, regulation or any NASDAQ listing standard. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc850955_27"></A>The Compensation Committee&#146;s Use of an Independent Compensation Consultant </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation Committee retains an independent compensation consultant to assist it in evaluating executive compensation programs and advise it regarding the amount
and form of executive and director compensation. It </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;30 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
uses a consultant to provide additional assurance that our executive and director compensation programs are reasonable, competitive and consistent with our objectives. It directly engages the
consultant under an engagement letter that the Compensation Committee reviews at least annually. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Since September 2009, the Compensation Committee has retained
Compensation Advisory Partners, LLC (&#147;CAP&#148;) as its independent compensation consultant, and the Compensation Committee annually reviews CAP&#146;s engagement. During 2014, CAP provided the Compensation Committee advice and services,
including: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

ended December&nbsp;31, 2014, CAP provided no services to Mondel&#275;z International other than consulting services to the Compensation Committee regarding executive and non-employee director compensation. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation Committee regularly reviews the current engagements and the objectivity and independence of the advice that CAP provides to the Compensation Committee
on executive and non-employee director compensation. The Compensation Committee considered the six specific independence factors adopted by the SEC and NASDAQ and determined that CAP is independent and that CAP&#146;s work did not raise any
conflicts of interest. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc850955_28"></A>Limited Role of Executive Officers in the Determination of Executive Compensation and Non-Employee Director
Compensation </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Each year, our CEO presents compensation recommendations for her direct reports and our other executive officers, including the NEOs. The Compensation Committee reviews and discusses these recommendations with the CEO,
but retains full discretion over these compensation actions. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Our CEO does not make recommendations or participate in deliberations regarding her own compensation. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Executive officers do not play a role in determining or recommending the amount or form of non-employee director compensation. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc850955_29"></A>How the Compensation Committee Manages Compensation-Related Risk </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">As it does each year, in 2014, the Compensation Committee evaluated whether our compensation designs, policies and practices operate to discourage our executive officers
and other employees from taking unnecessary or excessive risks. As described in the &#147;Compensation Discussion and Analysis,&#148; we design our compensation to incentivize executives and other employees to achieve the Company&#146;s financial
and strategic goals as well as individual performance goals that promote long-term shareholder returns. Our compensation design discourages our executives and other employees from taking excessive risks for short-term benefits that may harm the
Company and our shareholders in the long-term. The Compensation Committee uses various strategies to mitigate risk, including: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">using both short-term and long-term performance-based compensation so that executives do not focus solely on short-term performance; </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;31 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">weighting executive compensation heavily toward long-term incentive compensation to encourage sustainable shareholder value and accountability for long-term results; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">using multiple relevant performance measures in our incentive plan designs, so that executives do not place undue importance on one measure which could distort the results that we want to incent; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">weighting business and individual performance in our annual cash incentive program so that executives and employees do not have too narrow a focus; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">capping the amount of incentives that may be awarded or granted; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">retaining discretion to reduce incentive awards based on unforeseen or unintended consequences and clawback compensation in specified circumstances; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">requiring our top executives to hold a significant amount of their compensation in Company stock and prohibit them from hedging, pledging or engaging in short sales of their stock; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">not using employment contracts; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">not backdating or re-pricing option grants; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">not paying severance benefits on change in control unless the affected executive is first involuntarily terminated without cause or terminates due to good reason. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In addition, our Audit Committee oversees our ethics and compliance programs that educate executives and other employees on appropriate behavior and the consequences of
inappropriate actions. These programs not only drive compliance and integrity but also encourage employees with knowledge of bad behavior to report concerns by providing multiple reporting avenues while protecting reporting employees against
retaliation. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">CAP also reviewed the Compensation Committee&#146;s risk analysis, including the underlying procedures, and confirmed the Compensation
Committee&#146;s conclusion below. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In light of these analyses, the Compensation Committee believes that our compensation programs do not create risks that are
reasonably likely to have a material adverse effect on the Company. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:16pt; font-family:ARIAL"><A NAME="toc850955_30"></A>Compensation of Non-Employee Directors </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Any director who also is an employee of Mondel&#275;z International receives no compensation for service as a director. Currently, Irene B. Rosenfeld is the only
director who is an employee of the Company. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We strive to attract and retain highly qualified non-employee directors who will best represent our shareholders&#146;
interests. In order to ensure that the compensation offered is sufficient to meet this objective, our Compensation Committee periodically reviews non-employee director compensation. As in prior years, during 2014, the Compensation Committee used
data provided by CAP to benchmark our non-employee director compensation against our Compensation Survey Group and compensation paid to non-employee directors of Fortune 100 companies to assess the appropriateness of the form and amount of
non-employee director compensation and to make recommendations to the Board concerning such compensation. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Summary of Compensation Elements During 2014 </B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf" ALIGN="right">$15,000</TD>
<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD></TR>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;32 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Cash Compensation &#150; Board, Lead Director and Committee Chair Retainers </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We pay our non-employee directors their cash retainers quarterly. Pursuant to the Mondel&#275;z International, Inc. 2001 Compensation Plan for Non-Employee Directors,
they can defer 25%, 50%, 75% or 100% of their cash retainers into notional unfunded accounts that mirror certain of the investment options under the Mondel&#275;z Global LLC Thrift 401(k) Plan. If the Board appoints a non-employee director during
the year (i.e., other than at the annual meeting of shareholders), we pay that director a prorated retainer based on the number of days remaining in the calendar year. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Equity Compensation &#150; Annual Equity Grant </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Annual equity grants are made
following the annual meeting of shareholders. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">If the Board appoints a non-employee director during the year (i.e., other than at the annual meeting of
shareholders), the director receives a prorated equity grant upon appointment. We calculate the value of prorated grant using this ratio: the number of months until the next annual meeting of shareholders over a denominator of twelve months. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Non-employee director annual equity grants are made in the form of vested deferred stock units. Distribution of actual shares occurs six&nbsp;months after the director
ends his or her service as a director. When the Company pays a dividend on the Company&#146;s common shares, we accrue the value of the dividends that the Company would have paid on the deferred stock units. Six months after the director ends his or
her service as a director, we issue shares to the director equal to the accrued value. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Stock Holding Requirement </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">To align further the interests of our non-employee directors with our shareholders, we require our non-employee directors to hold shares of our common stock in an amount
equal to five times the annual Board retainer (i.e., $550,000) within five years of becoming a director. If a non-employee director does not meet the stock ownership requirement within that timeframe, the Lead Director will consider the non-employee
director&#146;s particular situation and may take action, as he deems appropriate. On March&nbsp;11, 2015, each director who has served for at least five years met or exceeded this requirement. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Company Match for Director Charitable Contributions </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Non-employee directors
are eligible to participate in a Mondel&#275;z International Foundation Matching Gift program. Each year, the Foundation will generally match up to $15,000 in contributions by a non-employee director to a 501(c)(3) non-profit organization(s). For
2014, the Foundation offered a two-for-one match promotion under which the Foundation contributed amounts over this general annual limit to non-profit organizations. </P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Overview </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>How our Financial Performance Impacted our
NEOs&#146; Annual and Long-Term Incentive Compensation Awards </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>2014 Annual Cash Incentive Program Awards</I><B> </B><I> </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">As illustrated below, we achieved the maximum rating (180%)&nbsp;on two of the three performance targets established by our Compensation Committee under our 2014 Annual
Cash Incentive Program&#150; Adjusted Earnings Per Share (&#147;EPS&#148;) stated at 2014 Plan Rates and Defined Free Cash Flow. On the third metric, Organic Net Revenue Growth, our performance (67% rating), while below target, was consistent with
the average of our Performance Peer Group (as defined below). The market share change overlay (new for 2014 and discussed in greater detail below) reduced our overall rating by 10 percentage points (&#147;pp&#148;). After taking the reduction for
the market share change overlay into account, our performance resulted in an above target rating of 125%. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g850955g88z69.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">See &#147;&#150; Description of Individual Executive Compensation Program Elements &#150; Financial Measure Definitions&#148; for
definitions of these performance measures and &#147;&#150; Description of Individual Executive Compensation Program Elements &#150; Annual Cash Incentive Program&#148; for more information about our Annual Cash Incentive Program, including our
performance targets under the program. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;35 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>2012-2014 Performance Cycle Awards </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Due to the spin off of our North American grocery business, Kraft Foods Group, Inc., to our shareholders on October&nbsp;1, 2012 (the &#147;Spin-Off&#148;), the
2012-2014 performance cycle for our performance share unit grants consisted of two performance periods: the nine month period from the start of the performance cycle to the Spin-Off (the &#147;Pre Spin-Off Period&#148;) and the twenty-seven month
period from the Spin-Off through the end of the performance cycle (the &#147;Post Spin-Off Period&#148;). </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">As illustrated below, we achieved solid annualized total
shareholder return (share price appreciation plus dividends) (&#147;TSR&#148;) relative to the median of the applicable Performance Peer Group (&#147;Annualized Relative Total Shareholder Return&#148;) for both the Pre Spin-Off Period (197% rating)
and Post Spin-Off Period (124% rating); strong Adjusted EPS Growth for both the Pre Spin-Off Period (200% rating, the maximum) and Post Spin-Off Period (200% rating, the maximum); and modest Organic Net Revenue Growth for both the Pre Spin-Off
Period (80% rating) and Post Spin-Off Period (0% rating). Overall, we achieved a weighted average performance rating of 126% of target for the 2012-2014 performance cycle. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g850955g68_36.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">See &#147;&#150; Description of Individual Executive Compensation Program Elements &#150; Financial Measure Definitions&#148; for
definitions of these performance measures and &#147; &#150; Description of Individual Executive Compensation Program Elements &#150; Equity Program&#148; for more information about our performance share units, including the performance targets. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Changes to our 2014 Executive Compensation Program/Preview of our 2015 Equity Program Change </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our Compensation Committee regularly assesses our executive compensation program in light of our strategy, market practices and shareholder feedback. In 2014, we made
changes to our executive compensation program. The changes took into account shareholder feedback and better align our executive compensation program with our strategies and objectives. Additionally, in 2015, we changed our annual equity program. We
summarize the changes below. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;36 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>2014 Executive Compensation Program Changes </I></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="18%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="40%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="40%"></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#4c4c4c" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Program</FONT></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Change</FONT></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Rationale</FONT></B></FONT></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"><I>2014 Annual Cash Incentive Program</I></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf"><I>Added a market share change overlay.</I> Depending on the market share increase or decrease in our key markets and categories, the overlay may increase or decrease the final rating by 10
pp.</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt">Aligns our NEOs&#146; compensation with our performance against our competitors in key markets and categories.</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"><I>2014-2016 Performance Share Unit Grant</I></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf"><I>Changed metrics.</I> Replaced &#147;Adjusted EPS Growth&#148; metric with &#147;Adjusted Return On Invested Capital Increase&#148;.</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt">Aligns our NEOs&#146; compensation with our performance against a metric used by investors to evaluate our return on capital performance
and stresses the importance of our continued focus on asset and cash management.</TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>2015 Equity Program Change </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">For the past
seven years through 2014, we allocated the total target grant value to senior executives under our annual equity program as follows: 50% performance share units; 25% non-qualified stock options; and 25% restricted stock. As illustrated below,
beginning with grants under our 2015 equity program, to further link pay to performance, we will allocate 75% of the total target grant value to performance share units and 25% to non-qualified stock options. We intend to no longer grant time-based
restricted stock to senior executives as part of our annual equity program. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Our Executive Compensation Program Received Strong Shareholder Support </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">More than 95% of the votes cast in our 2014 shareholder advisory Say on Pay vote supported our executive compensation program. Similarly, in 2014, more than 95% of votes
cast approved our Amended and Restated 2005 Performance Incentive Plan. As evidenced by these strong levels of support, we believe our shareholders generally support our overall compensation principles, programs and practices. Therefore, no changes
were made to our executive compensation program in response to the 2014 shareholder advisory Say on Pay vote. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
