 <div style="width:100%;margin-left:0%; margin-right:0%;background-color:#eaeaea;padding-top:2pt;padding-bottom:3pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Our Executive Compensation Design Principles and Governance Practices </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our executive compensation design principles and compensation governance practices reflect best practices to protect and promote our shareholders&#146; interests. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Design Principles. </I></B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="50%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="49%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" NOWRAP> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>What we do:</I></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><I>What we don&#146;t do:</I></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;<U>Link pay to performance</U>. We reward our NEOs</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">based upon the value they add.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT
STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Put pay at risk based on performance</U>. 84% of our CEO&#146;s pay and 74% of our other</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">NEOs&#146; pay is at-risk.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;<U>Target pay at the median of our peer group</U>. We</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">compensate fairly and competitively.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT
STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Set meaningful performance goals at the</U></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><U>beginning
of performance cycles</U>.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Intend that performance-based compensation</U></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><U>qualify for a tax deduction under Section&nbsp;162(m) of</U></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><U>the Code</U>.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#120;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;<U>Incent short-term results to the detriment of long-</U></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><U>term goals and results</U>.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT
STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#120;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Incent excessively risky business strategies</U>.</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Governance Practices. </I></B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="50%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="49%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" NOWRAP> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>What we do:</I></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><I>What we don&#146;t do:</I></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;<U>Require significant stock ownership</U>. Our stock</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">ownership guidelines are generally comparable</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">to, or more stringent than, those of our</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Compensation Survey Group companies.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;<U>Require executives to retain equity compensation</U>.</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We require our NEOs to hold for one year net</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">shares awarded and net shares acquired upon the</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">exercise of stock options.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;<U>Provide for &#147;clawbacks&#148;</U>. We can recoup incentive</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">compensation upon certain financial restatements.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT
STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Prohibit hedging, pledging and short sales</U>.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;<U>The Compensation Committee retains an</U></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><U>independent compensation consultant</U>. The</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">consultant does no work for the Company other</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">than advising the Compensation Committee.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ROWSPAN="2">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#120;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;<U>Provide NEOs with tax gross-ups for perquisites</U> or</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><U>upon a change in control</U>. Taxes are our NEOs&#146;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">responsibility.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-2.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#120;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Re-price underwater stock options</U>. We do not re-</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">price outstanding stock options, whether vested or</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">unvested.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-2.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#120;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Pay dividends on unvested performance share units</U></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><U>unless and until shares are earned</U>. We do not pay</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">accrued dividend equivalents unless and until the</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">applicable performance targets are met and we</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">award shares.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-2.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#120;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Enter into employment agreements with our NEOs</U>.</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We neither enter into employment agreements with</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">our NEOs, nor guarantee salary increases.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-2.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#120;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Provide separate, enhanced benefit plans for our</U></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><U>NEOs</U>. Our NEOs generally participate in the same</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">retirement, health and welfare plans broadly</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">available to salaried employees.</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;<U>Perform an annual compensation risk assessment</U>.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;<U>Engage with shareholders</U>. Regularly engage</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">shareholders through individual and small-group</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">meetings and major investor conferences.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;<U>Limit perquisites</U>. We offer perquisites comparable</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">to those provided by our Compensation Survey</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Group.</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Pay severance and vest equity upon a &#147;double</U></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><U>trigger&#148; in the event of a change in control</U>. &#147;Double</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">trigger&#148; requires both a change in control and</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">termination of the executive&#146;s employment without</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">cause or for good reason.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD></TR>
</TABLE> </div>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;39 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>How We Design our Executive Compensation Program </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In overseeing our executive compensation program, our Compensation Committee focuses on the following primary program goals: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">1.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">attract, retain and motivate talented executive officers and develop world-class business leaders; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">2.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">support business strategies that promote superior long-term shareholder returns; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">3.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">align pay and performance by making a significant portion of our NEOs&#146; compensation dependent on achieving financial and other critical strategic and individual goals; and </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">4.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">align our NEOs&#146; and shareholders&#146; interests through equity-based incentive grants that link executive compensation to sustained and superior TSR and stock ownership guidelines. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We design our executive compensation program to achieve these goals by: </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Using a Mix of Fixed and Variable Compensation.</I></B> We heavily weight the mix toward variable compensation for our NEOs to attract, retain and motivate
top-performing executives, as well as to appropriately align compensation levels with achieving relevant financial and strategic goals. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Using a Mix of Equity
and Cash Incentives.</I></B> We heavily weight the mix toward equity to focus NEOs on achieving long-term TSR that exceeds our peers&#146; median and to align with the interests of our shareholders. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Compensating based on Individual Performance and Potential.</I></B> We generally consider individual performance in making compensation decisions. We also
consider an executive&#146;s potential for advancement in making equity grants (other than performance share unit grants). </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Requiring NEOs to be Significant
Shareholders.</I></B> We require our NEOs to:<B><I> </I></B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Own specified levels of Company stock to align their interests with those of our shareholders. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Hold for one year net shares (after taxes and the payment of any exercise price) received upon the exercise of stock options, the removal of restrictions on restricted stock and the award of Company shares related to
performance share units. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Annually Benchmarking our Compensation Against Relevant Comparators.</I></B> We use two separate groups of companies
to benchmark the compensation that we offer to our NEOs and the performance that impacts our NEOs&#146; compensation: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Our Compensation Survey Group (global peers of similar size who are primarily consumer-facing); and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Our Performance Peer Group (industry peers). </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">With CAP&#146;s input, the Compensation Committee reviews the composition
of these comparator groups to ensure the composition of each remains appropriate. See &#147;&#150; Composition and Purpose of our Compensation Survey Group&#148; and &#147;&#150; Composition and Purpose of our Performance Peer Group&#148; below for
additional information. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Paying competitively.</I></B> Each year, we compare our compensation programs with those of our Compensation Survey Group. We assess
whether our executive compensation and target compensation levels are consistent with market practice. In addition, we compare our financial and TSR performance against our Performance Peer Group. The Performance Peer Group comparison allows us to
link long-term incentive compensation to the delivery of superior financial results relative to industry peers. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Composition and Purpose of our Compensation
Survey Group </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In constructing our Compensation Survey Group, our Compensation Committee considers global, top-tier companies with the following attributes: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Similar revenue size </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Similar market capitalization </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;40 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Primarily focused on food/beverage or consumer/household products or are consumer-facing companies </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Recognized for their industry leadership and brand recognition </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Executive positions similar in breadth, complexity and/or scope of responsibility </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Competitors for executive talent </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation Committee also considers companies outside the consumer products
industry based on the following criteria: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Revenue above $35 billion </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Competitive Positioning </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In determining
appropriate compensation levels for our NEOs, our Compensation Committee reviews compensation levels for similarly situated executives at companies in our Compensation Survey Group. Aon Hewitt (&#147;Aon&#148;) provides the compensation data. At the
request of the Compensation Committee, CAP reviews and evaluates Aon&#146;s data. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our Compensation Committee&#146;s compensation strategy is to benchmark total
direct compensation (at target), including base salary and annual and long-term incentives, at or near the median of our Compensation Survey Group. Company and individual performance will determine whether actual compensation received is above or
below the Compensation Survey Group median. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">To further validate our compensation levels, using data provided by CAP, our Compensation Committee retrospectively
evaluates how well we aligned pay-for-performance compared with our Compensation Survey Group. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Composition and Purpose of our Performance Peer Group </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Companies primarily focused on the production and marketing of food and non-alcoholic beverages comprise our 2014 Performance Peer Group listed below, which was
unchanged from 2013. Because we directly compete with these companies, comparing our performance with the group&#146;s median performance provides a valuable measure of our performance. Specifically, we compare our annualized TSR with the median
annualized TSR of our Performance Peer Group to assess our results on the TSR performance measure for our performance share units. This group is </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;41 </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Overview of 2014 Executive Compensation Program Elements </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">This table identifies and describes the specific elements of our 2014 executive compensation program for our NEOs, including each element&#146;s program objectives. A
more detailed discussion of these elements, including definitions of the financial measures used in our Annual Cash Incentive Program and grants of performance share units, follows this table. We discuss individual compensation decisions under
&#147;&#150; Compensation Paid to our Named Executive Officers in 2014.&#148; </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

individual contribution</P></TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">Each NEO receives a grant of performance share units at the outset of a three-year performance cycle. Actual awards are determined
at the end of the performance cycle by evaluating performance against pre-determined performance targets. Awards can be 0% to 200% of target, based on our performance. We deliver awards in Mondel&#275;z International common stock.</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Attract and retain talent</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Drive top-tier performance</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.50em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#150;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Across
entire organization</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.50em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#150;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Focus on long-term sustained success</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enhance stock ownership/align with
shareholders&#146; interests</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt">Restricted Stock</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">Each grant is based upon the NEO&#146;s role, long-term performance and potential for advancement. Restricted stock 100% vests
three years after the grant date. Restricted stock will not be part of the annual equity program beginning in 2015 for senior executives. However, we will continue to use it for specific retention efforts.</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Attract and retain talent</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Drive top-tier performance</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.50em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#150;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Through
long-term individual contribution</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.50em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#150;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Recognize advancement potential</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enhance stock ownership/align with
shareholders&#146; interests</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt">Non-Qualified Stock&nbsp;Options</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Each grant is based upon the NEO&#146;s role,
long-term performance and potential for advancement. Non-qualified stock options (&#147;NQSOs&#148;) vest:</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#150;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;33% on the first and second anniversary of the grant date; and</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#150;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;34% on the
third anniversary of the grant date.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Attract and retain talent</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Drive top-tier performance</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.50em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#150;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Through

<P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Deferred Compensation and Executive Perquisites</B></P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Voluntary Non-Qualified</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Deferred Compensation</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Plan</P></TD>

future financial goals.</TD>

security</P></TD></TR>

use of the Company&#146;s aircraft.</TD>

<P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Retirement and Separation Benefits</B></P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt">Defined&nbsp;Benefit&nbsp;Program&nbsp;(i.e., Pension)</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">Generally, provides for the replacement of a portion of cash compensation (defined as base salary plus annual cash incentive
award) after the NEO retires. We do not offer this program to any U.S. employees hired after 2008 and we will make no additional accruals after 2019 for current participants. In addition to the tax-qualified defined benefit program, we also provide
a supplemental nonqualified defined benefit program to account for the qualified plan limits under the Code.</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>

<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Provide financial security to long-term service
executive officers in retirement</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Defined Contribution&nbsp;Program</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">(i.e., 401(k) Savings)</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">Program under which Company matches U.S. NEO contributions up to a limit. Account balances are typically payable after an NEO
terminates employment. We enhanced this program for U.S. employees hired after 2008 who are not eligible for the defined benefit program described above. In addition to the tax-qualified defined contribution program, we also provide a supplemental
defined contribution program to account for certain deferral and compensation limits applicable to qualified plans under the Code.</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt">

financial security in retirement</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Provide U.S. executive officers an additional means
to meet stock ownership requirements</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Change in</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Control
Plan</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>

of time after a change in control.</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>

<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Focus on delivering top-tier shareholder value in
periods of uncertainty</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Support effective transition</P></TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt">Other Benefits</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Attract and retain talent</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Provide death benefits to NEO&#146;s
beneficiaries</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Description of Individual Executive Compensation Program Elements </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Base Salary </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Base salary is the principal fixed element of executive
compensation. In setting base salaries for our NEOs, our Compensation Committee generally targets base salary at or near the median of our Compensation Survey Group based on the executive&#146;s corresponding role. Our Compensation Committee also
considers a number of other factors when setting base salaries for our NEOs, including Company and individual performance, level of responsibility, potential to assume roles with greater responsibility and experience. The Compensation Committee
reviews our NEOs&#146; salaries annually (or more often if there is a notable change in an executive officer&#146;s role and responsibilities during the course of the year) and considers whether any increases are warranted. If so, salary increases
are generally effective April&nbsp;1 for all executive officers. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Annual Cash Incentive Program </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We design our Annual Cash Incentive Program to motivate our NEOs and to reward them for delivering results above the threshold performance of our annual financial and
strategic goals. The Compensation Committee sets the formula and each NEO&#146;s target and maximum annual incentive opportunity at the beginning of the year. The Compensation Committee bases actual awards made to an NEO on our annual financial
results and the NEO&#146;s individual performance. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;44 </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Annual Cash Incentive Program Award Formula </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation Committee used the formula below to determine awards made to NEOs under the 2014 Annual Cash Incentive Program. See &#147;&#150; Compensation Paid to
our Named Executive Officers in 2014&#148; for additional detail on the actual awards made to each NEO. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g850955g28w24.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">This chart describes the Annual Cash Incentive Program elements, except for base salary (discussed above). </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="80%"></TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>

<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Target Annual Incentive</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Opportunity</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">2014 target percentage of base salary reflects each
NEO&#146;s role and responsibilities.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ms. Rosenfeld: 150%</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Gladden: 100% (prorated for 2014 based on his
October 13, 2014 hire date)</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Brearton: 90%</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;All Other NEOs: 80%</P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#e5e5e5" STYLE="font-size:1px; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:6pt">

<P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>

collaboration and range from 0% to 180%.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">In early 2014, the Compensation Committee approved the

<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Additionally, in 2014, the Compensation Committee added a market share change overlay to measure our
performance against competitors in key markets and categories. Depending on actual performance, the market share change overlay adjusts the corporate rating in one of three ways: no change, 10 pp increase, or 10 pp decrease.</P>

<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(1)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The market share change overlay reflects our net revenue weighted market share change in our global categories, including biscuits, chocolate, gum and candy, and major regional categories, including coffee and cream
cheese in Europe, powdered beverages in Latin America and Asia Pacific, and coffee in Eastern Europe, Middle East and Africa. A market share decrease of more than 10 basis points (&#147;bps&#148;) results in a 10 pp decrease to the performance
rating, while an increase of more than 35 bps results in a 10 pp increase to the performance rating. For 2014, our market share decreased more than 10 bps resulting in a 10 pp decrease to the performance rating, as reflected in the table above.
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation Committee retains discretionary authority to adjust the actual corporate rating (up or down) by as much as 25 pp to recognize more
subjective, less quantifiable factors&#151;such as how well we performed based on innovation, portfolio management, talent management and the quality of our results. The Compensation Committee did not exercise this authority to adjust the 2014
rating. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Equity Program </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We design our equity grants to align our
executive officers&#146; and shareholders&#146; interests. For our 2014 equity program, the Compensation Committee continued to use the mix it has used since 2008, which is 50% performance share units, 25% restricted stock and 25% NQSOs. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g850955g00p46.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Performance Share Units </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation
Committee grants performance share units to motivate executives to achieve our long-term financial goals and deliver top-tier shareholder returns. The Compensation Committee sets performance targets for a three-year performance cycle. The grants
made in 2014 are for the three-year period ending December&nbsp;31, 2016, and the 2014-2016 and 2012-2014 outstanding performance cycles are discussed in greater detail below. At the end of the three-year performance cycle, the Compensation
Committee will only award shares if results meet or exceed the performance thresholds it set at the beginning of the cycle. The number of shares awarded to an executive </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;46 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
depends on the achievement of key financial measures and annualized TSR relative to the median of our Performance Peer Group. An award generally occurs in the first quarter following the end of
the performance cycle, provided the Compensation Committee certifies performance at or above threshold levels. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">To address unforeseen or unintended consequences,
the Compensation Committee retains discretion to adjust the final business performance rating for a performance cycle (up or down) by as much as 25 pp, allowing the Compensation Committee to factor in a subjective review of quality of financial
results, portfolio management, innovation and talent development. The Compensation Committee did not exercise its discretion to make a limited adjustment for the 2012-2014 performance cycle. The Compensation Committee does not consider an NEO&#146;s
individual contributions as the basis for an award; awards related to performance share units are based solely on how the Company performed against performance targets. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Dividend equivalents are not paid or accrued on unvested performance share units for grants made prior to 2013. For grants made in 2013 and 2014, dividend equivalents
accrue during the performance period and will be paid out in cash in the first quarter following the award date based on the actual share award. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation
Committee uses the following formula to determine actual awards for participants, including our NEOs. Other than base salary, each element of this formula is discussed below. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g850955g72p16.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>2014-2016 Performance Cycle </I></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="28%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="70%"></TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>

target number of performance share units based on a percentage of his or her base salary at the beginning of the performance cycle (January 1, 2014). The percentages of base salary for the NEOs (except Mr. Gladden) were as follows:</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;47 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">For performance share units with a 2014-2016 performance cycle, the target objective set for Annualized Relative Total
Shareholder Return is the median of the Performance Peer Group. We set our financial performance targets for Organic Net Revenue Growth and Adjusted ROIC Increase taking into consideration our long-term strategy. We do not publicly disclose specific
financial performance targets on a prospective basis. Revealing these specific targets prospectively would provide competitors and other third parties with insights into our confidential planning process and strategies, thereby potentially harming
us competitively. The financial performance targets are designed to be challenging, and there is a risk that awards will not be made at all or will be made at less than 100% of the target award level. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We base cash awards under our Annual Cash Incentive Program and share awards for our performance share units in part on our Organic Net Revenue Growth. However, the
Compensation Committee uses a different benchmark to measure performance for each. For the Annual Cash Incentive Program, the Compensation Committee measures Organic Net Revenue Growth based on our annual operating targets. In contrast, when setting
our Organic Net Revenue Growth target for the 2014-2016 performance cycle, the Compensation Committee considered our long-term strategy. The Compensation Committee believes the use of these different targets focuses our executives on critical
internal drivers, both in the short- and long-term, and that the different targets for each, when combined, closely correlate with shareholder value. Additionally, the majority of any cash award under our Annual Cash Incentive Program or share award
for the 2014-2016 performance cycle is based on separate independent performance measures, as Organic Net Revenue Growth is weighted 40% for our Annual Cash Incentive Program and 25% for our 2014-2016 performance cycle. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>2012-2014 Performance Cycle </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In connection with the Spin-Off, the
Compensation Committee adjusted each outstanding performance share unit for the 2012-2014 performance cycle using a conversion ratio of 1.5266. Without this adjustment, the Spin-Off would have adversely affected executives&#146; outstanding
performance share unit grants. The adjustment normalized the potential value of each Post Spin-Off performance share unit with that of each Pre Spin-Off performance share unit because, unlike an outstanding share of restricted stock or non-qualified
stock option, a performance share unit did not provide a holder with any value relating to the Spin-Off. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our Compensation Committee determined the share award for
the 2012-2014 performance cycle based on a weighted average performance rating that included the Company&#146;s performance during both the Pre Spin-Off Period and Post Spin-Off Period. For both periods, the Compensation Committee used the same
performance measures and weightings of key financial goals (Organic Net Revenue Growth and Adjusted EPS Growth) and Annualized Relative Total Shareholder Return goals. However, the Compensation Committee did adjust the targets for the Post Spin-Off
Period to reflect our Post Spin-Off attributes. With regard to determining our Annualized Relative Total Shareholder Return performance, we used our Pre Spin-Off Performance Peer Group, which consisted of the following companies, to assess results
until the Spin-Off: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Restricted Stock and Non-Qualified Stock Options </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In 2014, we delivered 25%
of our NEOs&#146; total target grant value in restricted stock and 25% in NQSOs. This equity mix balances the retention value of restricted stock with the performance-related value of NQSOs. To maintain this balance, based on a Black-Scholes
valuation, the Compensation Committee maintained the ratio of restricted stock grants to NQSO grants at one to five, the same ratio used in 2013. U.S. employees on international assignment, </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;49 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
such as Mr.&nbsp;Cofer, receive grants of deferred stock units instead of restricted stock, which have the same vesting schedule as restricted stock. We pay dividends on unvested restricted stock
and dividend equivalents on deferred stock units at a similar time and the same rate as dividends paid on Mondel&#275;z International common stock generally. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The
Compensation Committee bases grant ranges for restricted stock and NQSOs on an analysis of competitive market practice, with the midpoint of the equity grant ranges, inclusive of the value of the target performance share units, approximately equal
to the total long-term incentive median of our Compensation Survey Group. It may make an equity grant of restricted stock and NQSOs above or below the midpoint based on its qualitative review of the executive officer&#146;s individual performance
and its evaluation of the executive officer&#146;s potential to assume roles with greater responsibility. Generally, the aggregate grant value for restricted stock and NQSOs is between 50% and 150% of the midpoint. All annual equity grants made to
our NEOs in 2014 fell within that range. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The table below shows the NEO grant value ranges for restricted stock and NQSOs for the 2014 annual equity grant on
February&nbsp;19, 2014. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Because Mr.&nbsp;Gladden was hired on October&nbsp;13, 2014, he did not receive a 2014 annual equity grant and therefore is not included in the table above. However, Mr.&nbsp;Gladden did receive sign-on equity grants in

<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We present actual equity grants in the 2014 Grants of Plan-Based Awards table under &#147;Executive Compensation Tables&#148; in this Proxy Statement. The annual grant
date for restricted stock and NQSOs is pre-determined based on the scheduled date of the Compensation Committee meeting following the release of our annual financial results. The exercise price for the annual 2014 NQSO grants was determined on the
date the Compensation Committee approved the grants and was the average of the high and low trading prices on that date<I>.</I> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>2012 CEO Equity Grant </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In December 2012, the Compensation Committee made Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld a special equity grant. The grant consisted of restricted stock (20% of grant), which fully vests on
December&nbsp;19, 2015, and performance-contingent restricted stock units (80% of grant). The performance-contingent restricted stock units hinged on Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld satisfying specified retention requirements and the Mondel&#275;z International
share price exceeding specific price thresholds for a minimum of 10 consecutive trading days. During 2013, the first two share price thresholds ($31.12 and $33.72) were met and, in 2014, the final share price threshold ($36.31) was met. Even though
all share price thresholds have been met, Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld will not receive any award of Company shares in connection with the performance-contingent restricted stock units prior to December&nbsp;19, 2015. Like all NEO equity awards, shares
awarded to Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld under the special equity grant are subject to the&nbsp;minimum one-year holding requirement described in greater detail below. In addition, Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld is subject to more stringent holding requirements for the
last tranche of shares awarded under the performance-contingent restricted stock units (equal to 37.5% of the grant), as she must hold those shares for at least one year after she ceases to be CEO. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Requiring Stock Ownership </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">To further align our NEOs&#146; and our
shareholders&#146; interests, and to incent our NEOs to focus on shareholder interests, the Compensation Committee requires each executive to acquire and hold a significant amount of our common stock. The following chart summarizes our stock
ownership and holding requirements. We believe our stock ownership requirements are comparable to, or are more stringent than, stock ownership requirements of the majority of our Compensation Survey Group. We regularly monitor compliance with these
levels. As of March&nbsp;1, 2015, each of our NEOs satisfied the ownership and holding requirements described below, except for Mr.&nbsp;Gladden. He has five years from his October&nbsp;13, 2014 hire date to comply. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;50 </FONT></P>

<TR BGCOLOR="#4c4c4c" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Key Provisions</FONT></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Explanation of Key Provisions</FONT></B></FONT></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"><B>Ownership Requirement</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Eight times salary for our CEO.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Four times salary for our other NEOs.</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"><B>Time to Meet Requirements</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt">
<P STYLE="margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Five years from employment date or three years from promotion to executive level
subject to requirements.</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"><B>Shares Included As Ownership</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mondel&#275;z International common stock, including
sole ownership, direct purchase plan shares, qualified savings plans, restricted stock, deferred stock units and accounts over which the executive has direct or indirect ownership or control.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Excludes unexercised Mondel&#275;z International
stock options and outstanding performance share units.</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"><B>Holding Requirements</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Until they meet stock ownership guidelines, our NEOs
must hold 100% of all shares acquired under our equity program (including stock after the restrictions have lapsed, shares awarded for our vested deferred stock units, shares acquired upon exercise of a NQSO and shares awarded for our performance
share units), net of shares withheld for taxes or payment of exercise price.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Once an NEO meets stock ownership requirements,
assuming he or she is also an executive officer, the NEO must hold 100% of the shares, net of shares withheld for taxes or payment of exercise price, for at least one year after the stock option exercise or receipt of shares awarded under our equity
program.</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Financial Measure Definitions </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">While we
report our financial results in accordance with U.S. GAAP, we use non-GAAP financial measures in making financial, operating and planning decisions and in evaluating our performance. Therefore, we also base financial targets for our Annual Cash
Incentive Program and grants of performance share units on non-GAAP and other financial measures. The chart below describes adjustments to the related GAAP measure and our reasons for using these measures. (See our Annual Report on Form 10-K for the
year ended December&nbsp;31, 2014, for additional information on our Non-GAAP Financial Measures and definitions of terms used in the Definitions column below.) </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt">Defined Free Cash Flow</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="3" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Free Cash Flow (Net Cash Provided By Operating Activities less capital expenditures) excluding:</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;taxes paid on the Starbucks arbitration,</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;cash payments made for accrued interest and other
related fees associated with the debt tendered on February&nbsp;6, 2014, and</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;cash payments (net of tax benefits) associated with
Spin-Off Costs, 2012-2014 Restructuring Program expenditures, 2014-2018 Restructuring Program expenditures and incremental costs associated with the JDE coffee transactions.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt">Reflects financial liquidity, working capital efficiency and financial health.</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt">Adjusted ROIC Increase</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="3" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">Adjusted Net Operating Profit (&#147;NOPAT&#148;) divided by Invested Capital, which are defined below.</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ROWSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt">Reflects a metric used to evaluate the performance of capital deployment and stresses the importance of continued focus on asset
and cash management.</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">NOPAT is defined as Operating Income less taxes excluding the impacts of:</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Spin-Off costs,</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;pension costs related to the obligations transferred
in the Spin-Off,</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;the 2012-2014 Restructuring Program,</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;the 2014-2018 Restructuring Program<SUP
STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(2)</SUP>,</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;the Integration Program and other acquisition integration costs,</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;the remeasurement of net monetary assets in

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;52 </FONT></P>
